msgstr "3. The third training rule on the robe-making season"

#. </h1></div><h2>
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np3:6.1"
msgid ""
msgstr "Origin story"

#. </h2><p><a class="sc" id="1"></a><a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pi3.203"></a><a class="pts-cs" id="bu-np.3.1"></a><a class="pts-cs" id="bu-np.3.1.1"></a><a class="pts-vp-en" id="bd.2.24"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="1921"></a> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np3:6.2"
msgid "Tena samayena buddho bhagavā sāvatthiyaṃ viharati jetavane anāthapiṇḍikassa ārāme."
msgstr "At one time the Buddha was staying at Sāvatthī in the Jeta Grove, Anāthapiṇḍika’s Monastery."

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np3:6.3"
msgid "Tena kho pana samayena aññatarassa bhikkhuno akālacīvaraṃ uppannaṃ hoti."
msgstr "At that time a monk had been offered robe-cloth outside the robe season."

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np3:6.4"
msgid "Tassa taṃ cīvaraṃ kayiramānaṃ nappahoti."
msgstr "While he was making the robe, he realized there was not enough cloth."

#. <span class="note" hidden>The point, according to the commentary, is that he was trying to increase its size.</span> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np3:6.5"
msgid "Atha kho so bhikkhu taṃ cīvaraṃ ussāpetvā punappunaṃ vimajjati."
msgstr "Lifting it up, he smoothed it out again and again."

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np3:6.6"
msgid "Addasā kho bhagavā senāsanacārikaṃ āhiṇḍanto taṃ bhikkhuṃ taṃ cīvaraṃ ussāpetvā punappunaṃ vimajjantaṃ."
msgstr "While inspecting the dwellings, the Master saw that monk acting in this way."

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np3:6.7"
msgid "Disvāna yena so bhikkhu tenupasaṅkami;"
msgstr "He approached him"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np3:6.8"
msgid "upasaṅkamitvā taṃ bhikkhuṃ etadavoca—"
msgstr "and said,"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np3:6.9"
msgid "“kissa tvaṃ, bhikkhu, imaṃ cīvaraṃ ussāpetvā punappunaṃ vimajjasī”ti?"
msgstr "“What are you doing, monk?”"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np3:6.10"
msgid "“Idaṃ me, bhante, akālacīvaraṃ uppannaṃ."
msgstr "“Venerable Sir, I have received this robe-cloth outside the robe season,"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np3:6.11"
msgid "Kayiramānaṃ nappahoti."
msgstr "but it’s not enough to make a robe."

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np3:6.12"
msgid "Tenāhaṃ imaṃ cīvaraṃ ussāpetvā punappunaṃ vimajjāmī”ti."
msgstr "That’s why I lift it up and smooth it out again and again.”"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np3:6.13"
msgid "“Atthi pana te, bhikkhu, cīvarapaccāsā”ti?"
msgstr "“Are you expecting to receive more cloth?”"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np3:6.14"
msgid "“Atthi, bhagavā”ti."
msgstr "“I am.”"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np3:6.15"
msgid "Atha kho bhagavā etasmiṃ nidāne etasmiṃ pakaraṇe dhammiṃ kathaṃ katvā, bhikkhū āmantesi—"
msgstr "Soon afterwards the Master gave a teaching and addressed the monks:"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np3:6.16"
msgid "“anujānāmi, bhikkhave, akālacīvaraṃ paṭiggahetvā cīvarapaccāsā nikkhipitun”ti."
msgstr "“Monks, I allow you to keep out-of-season robe-cloth if you are expecting to receive more.”"

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="2"></a><a class="pts-cs" id="bu-np.3.1.2"></a><a class="pts-vp-en" id="bd.2.25"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="1922"></a> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np3:7.1"
msgid "Tena kho pana samayena bhikkhū—“bhagavatā anuññātaṃ akālacīvaraṃ paṭiggahetvā cīvarapaccāsā nikkhipitun”ti"
msgstr "When they knew that the Master had given this allowance,"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np3:7.2"
msgid "akālacīvarāni paṭiggahetvā atirekamāsaṃ nikkhipanti."
msgstr "some monks kept robe-cloth for over a month,"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np3:7.3"
msgid "Tāni cīvarāni cīvaravaṃse bhaṇḍikābaddhāni tiṭṭhanti."
msgstr "in a bundle on a bamboo robe-rack."

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np3:7.4"
msgid "Addasā kho āyasmā ānando senāsanacārikaṃ āhiṇḍanto tāni cīvarāni cīvaravaṃse bhaṇḍikābaddhāni tiṭṭhante."
msgstr "While inspecting the dwellings Venerable Ānanda saw that robe-cloth,"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np3:7.5"
msgid "Disvāna bhikkhū āmantesi—"
msgstr "and he asked the monks,"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np3:7.6"
msgid "“kassimāni, āvuso, cīvarāni cīvaravaṃse bhaṇḍikābaddhāni tiṭṭhantī”ti?"
msgstr "“Whose robe-cloth is this?”"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np3:7.7"
msgid "“Amhākaṃ, āvuso, akālacīvarāni cīvarapaccāsā nikkhittānī”ti."
msgstr "“It’s our out-of-season robe-cloth, which we’re keeping because we’re expecting more.”"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np3:7.8"
msgid "“Kīvaciraṃ panāvuso, imāni cīvarāni nikkhittānī”ti?"
msgstr "“How long have you kept this cloth?”"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np3:7.9"
msgid "“Atirekamāsaṃ, āvuso”ti."
msgstr "“Over a month.”"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np3:7.10"
msgid "Āyasmā ānando ujjhāyati khiyyati vipāceti—"
msgstr "Venerable Ānanda complained and criticized them,"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np3:7.11"
msgid "“kathañhi nāma bhikkhū akālacīvaraṃ paṭiggahetvā atirekamāsaṃ nikkhipissantī”ti."
msgstr "“How can these monks keep out-of-season robe-cloth for over a month?”"

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="3"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="1923"></a> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np3:8.1"
msgid "Atha kho āyasmā ānando te bhikkhū anekapariyāyena vigarahitvā bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesi … pe …"
msgstr "After criticizing those monks in many ways, Venerable Ānanda informed the Master. …"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np3:8.2"
msgid "“saccaṃ kira, bhikkhave, bhikkhū akālacīvaraṃ paṭiggahetvā atirekamāsaṃ nikkhipantī”ti?"
msgstr "“Is it true, monks, that some monks do this?”"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np3:8.3"
msgid "“Saccaṃ, bhagavā”ti."
msgstr "“It’s true, Master.”"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np3:8.4"
msgid "Vigarahi buddho bhagavā … pe …"
msgstr "The Buddha criticized them, “…"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np3:8.5"
msgid "kathañhi nāma te, bhikkhave, moghapurisā akālacīvaraṃ paṭiggahetvā atirekamāsaṃ nikkhipissanti."
msgstr "How can these foolish men keep out-of-season robe-cloth for over a month?"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np3:8.6"
msgid "Netaṃ, bhikkhave, appasannānaṃ vā pasādāya … pe …"
msgstr "This will not give rise to confidence in those without it …"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np3:8.7"
msgid "evañca pana, bhikkhave, imaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ uddiseyyātha—"
msgstr "And, monks, this training rule should be recited thus:"

#. </p><h2>
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np3:9.1"
msgid ""
msgstr "Final ruling"

#. </h2><p><a class="sc" id="4"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="1924"></a><a class="pts-vp-en" id="bd.2.26"></a>
#. <strong class="rule">
#. <span class="note" hidden><i lang="pi">Cīvara</i> means both a finished robe and any cloth that can be used to make a robe. Thus I vary my translation depending on the context. Sometimes it means both, and I then render it as robe(-cloth).</span> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np3:9.2"
msgid "“Niṭṭhitacīvarasmiṃ bhikkhunā ubbhatasmiṃ kathine bhikkhuno paneva akālacīvaraṃ uppajjeyya, ākaṅkhamānena bhikkhunā paṭiggahetabbaṃ."
msgstr "‘When his robe is finished and the robe-making season has ended, if out-of-season robe-cloth becomes available to a monk, he may receive it if he wishes."

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np3:9.3"
msgid "Paṭiggahetvā khippameva kāretabbaṃ."
msgstr "If he receives it, he should quickly make a robe."

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np3:9.4"
msgid "No cassa pāripūri, māsaparamaṃ tena bhikkhunā taṃ cīvaraṃ nikkhipitabbaṃ ūnassa pāripūriyā satiyā paccāsāya."
msgstr "If there is not enough cloth, but he is expecting more, he should keep it at most one month to make up the lack."

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np3:9.5"
msgid "Tato ce uttari nikkhipeyya, satiyāpi paccāsāya, nissaggiyaṃ pācittiyan”ti."
msgstr "If he keeps it beyond that, even if he expects more cloth, he commits an offense entailing relinquishment and confession.’”"

#. </strong> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np3:9.6"
msgid "(<em>3</em>:<strong>22</strong>)"
msgstr ""

#. </p><h2>
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np3:10.1"
msgid ""
msgstr "Definitions"

#. </h2><p><a class="sc" id="5"></a><a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pi3.204"></a><a class="pts-cs" id="bu-np.3.2"></a><a class="pts-cs" id="bu-np.3.2.1"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="1925"></a>
#. <strong class="term"> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np3:10.2"
msgid "Niṭṭhitacīvarasminti"
msgstr "When his robe is finished:"

#. </strong><span class="gloss">
#. <span class="note" hidden>This refers to robe-cloth received during the robe-making season. For details see <span class="ref">Mv.7.2-7.12</span>.</span> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np3:10.3"
msgctxt "bhikkhuno cīvaraṃ kataṃ vā hoti naṭṭhaṃ vā vinaṭṭhaṃ vā daḍḍhaṃ vā cīvarāsā vā upacchinnā."
msgstr "the monk has made a robe, or the robe-cloth has been lost, destroyed, or burnt, or he has abandoned his expectation of receiving further robe-cloth."

#. </span></p><p><a class="sc" id="6"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="1926"></a>
#. <strong class="term"> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np3:11.1"
msgid "Ubbhatasmiṃ kathineti"
msgstr "The robe-making season has ended:"

#. </strong><span class="gloss">
#. <span class="note" hidden>For an explanation of this see <span class="ref">Mv.7.1.7</span> and <span class="ref">Mv.7.2-7.12</span>.</span> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np3:11.2"
msgctxt "aṭṭhannaṃ mātikānaṃ aññatarāya mātikāya ubbhataṃ hoti, saṃghena vā antarā ubbhataṃ hoti."
msgstr "it has ended according to one of the eight headings or the Order has ended it, whichever comes first."

#. </span></p><p><a class="sc" id="7"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="1927"></a>
#. <strong class="term"> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np3:12.1"
msgid "Akālacīvaraṃ nāma"
msgstr "Out-of-season robe-cloth:"

#. </strong><span class="gloss">
#. <span class="note" hidden>That is, in-season robe-cloth is cloth obtained during the last month of the rainy season, while out-of-season robe-cloth is cloth obtained during the remaining eleven months of the year. See <span class="ref">Kkh. 101.28</span>.</span> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np3:12.2"
msgctxt "anatthate kathine ekādasamāse uppannaṃ,"
msgstr "if the robe-making ceremony has not been performed, robe-cloth that becomes available during the eleven months."

#. <span class="note" hidden>That is, in-season robe-cloth is cloth obtained during the last month of the rainy season or during the cold season, while out-of-season robe-cloth is cloth obtained during the remaining seven months of the year. See <span class="ref">Kkh.101.28</span>.</span> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np3:12.3"
msgctxt "atthate kathine sattamāse uppannaṃ,"
msgstr "If the robe-making ceremony has been performed, robe-cloth that becomes available during the seven months."

#. <span class="note" hidden>See <span class="ref">Kkh.102.1</span>.</span> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np3:12.4"
msgctxt "kālepi ādissa dinnaṃ, etaṃ akālacīvaraṃ nāma."
msgstr "Also, if it is given in the robe season, but it is designated as out-of-season cloth, it is called “out-of-season robe-cloth.”"

#. </span></p><p><a class="sc" id="8"></a><a class="pts-vp-en" id="bd.2.27"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="1928"></a>
#. <strong class="term"> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np3:13.1"
msgid "Uppajjeyyāti"
msgstr "Becomes available:"

#. </strong><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np3:13.2"
msgctxt "uppajjeyya saṃghato vā gaṇato vā ñātito vā mittato vā paṃsukūlaṃ vā attano vā dhanena."
msgstr "becomes available from the Order, from a group, from a relative, or from a friend, or if rags become available, or it becomes available by means his own property."

#. </span></p><p><a class="sc" id="9"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="1929"></a>
#. <strong class="term"> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np3:14.1"
msgid "Ākaṅkhamānenāti"
msgstr "If he wishes:"

#. </strong><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np3:14.2"
msgctxt "icchamānena paṭiggahetabbaṃ."
msgstr "if he desires, he may receive it."

#. </span></p><p><a class="sc" id="10"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="1930"></a>
#. <strong class="term"> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np3:15.1"
msgid "Paṭiggahetvā khippameva kāretabbanti"
msgstr "If he receives it, he should quickly make a robe:"

#. </strong><span class="gloss">
#. <span class="note" hidden>That is, in accordance with the first rule of this section, <span class="ref">Relinquishment 1</span>.</span> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np3:15.2"
msgctxt "dasāhā kāretabbaṃ."
msgstr "it should be made within ten days."

#. </span></p><p><a class="sc" id="11"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="1931"></a>
#. <strong class="term"> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np3:16.1"
msgid "No cassa pāripūrīti"
msgstr "If there is not enough cloth:"

#. </strong><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np3:16.2"
msgctxt "kayiramānaṃ nappahoti."
msgstr "if there is not enough cloth when the robe is being made."

#. </span></p><p><a class="sc" id="12"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="1932"></a>
#. <strong class="term"> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np3:17.1"
msgid "Māsaparamaṃ tena bhikkhunā taṃ cīvaraṃ nikkhipitabbanti"
msgstr "He should keep it at most one month:"

#. </strong><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np3:17.2"
msgctxt "māsaparamatā nikkhipitabbaṃ."
msgstr "he should keep it for one month at the maximum."

#. </span></p><p><a class="sc" id="13"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="1933"></a>
#. <strong class="term"> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np3:18.1"
msgid "Ūnassa pāripūriyāti"
msgstr "To make up the lack:"

#. </strong><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np3:18.2"
msgctxt "ūnassa pāripūratthāya."
msgstr "for the purpose of making up the lack."

#. </span></p><p><a class="sc" id="14"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="1934"></a>
#. <strong class="term"> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np3:19.1"
msgid "Satiyā paccāsāyāti"
msgstr "But he is expecting more:"

#. </strong><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np3:19.2"
msgctxt "paccāsā hoti saṃghato vā gaṇato vā ñātito vā mittato vā paṃsukūlaṃ vā attano vā dhanena."
msgstr "he is expecting more from the Order, from a group, from a relative, or from a friend, or he is expecting to get rags, or he is expecting to get it by means of his own property."

#. </span></p><p><a class="sc" id="15"></a><a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pi3.205"></a><a class="pts-cs" id="bu-np.3.2.2"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="1935"></a>
#. <strong class="term"> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np3:20.1"
msgid "Tato ce uttari nikkhipeyya satiyāpi paccāsāyāti"
msgstr "If he keeps it beyond that, even if he expects more cloth:"

#. </strong><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np3:20.2"
msgctxt "tadahuppanne mūlacīvare paccāsācīvaraṃ uppajjati, dasāhā kāretabbaṃ."
msgstr "If he receives the expected robe-cloth on the same day as when he received the original robe-cloth, it must be made into a robe within ten days."

#. <span class="note" hidden>The Pali idiom is such that this means on the day after he received the original piece of cloth. (Cf. the definition of ten days in Relinquishment 1, where the eleventh dawn means the tenth dawn after one received the cloth.) The way this works, it seems, is that the day on which the cloth was received counts as one.</span> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np3:20.3"
msgid "Dvīhuppanne mūlacīvare paccāsācīvaraṃ uppajjati, dasāhā kāretabbaṃ."
msgstr "If he receives the expected robe-cloth two days after he received the original robe-cloth, it must be made into a robe within ten days."

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np3:20.4"
msgid "Tīhuppanne mūlacīvare … pe …"
msgstr "If he receives the expected robe-cloth three days after …"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np3:20.5"
msgid "catūhuppanne …"
msgstr "four days after …"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np3:20.6"
msgid "pañcāhuppanne …"
msgstr "five days after …"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np3:20.7"
msgid "chāhuppanne …"
msgstr "six days after …"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np3:20.8"
msgid "sattāhuppanne …"
msgstr "seven days after …"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np3:20.9"
msgid "aṭṭhāhuppanne …"
msgstr "eight days after …"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np3:20.10"
msgid "navāhuppanne …"
msgstr "nine days after …"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np3:20.11"
msgid "dasāhuppanne mūlacīvare paccāsācīvaraṃ uppajjati, dasāhā kāretabbaṃ."
msgstr "ten days after …"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np3:20.12"
msgid "Ekādase uppanne … pe …"
msgstr "eleven days after …"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np3:20.13"
msgid "dvādase uppanne …"
msgstr "twelve days after …"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np3:20.14"
msgid "terase uppanne …"
msgstr "thirteen days after …"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np3:20.15"
msgid "cuddase uppanne …"
msgstr "fourteen days after …"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np3:20.16"
msgid "pannarase uppanne …"
msgstr "fifteen days after …"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np3:20.17"
msgid "soḷase uppanne …"
msgstr "sixteen days after …"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np3:20.18"
msgid "sattarase uppanne …"
msgstr "seventeen days after …"

#. <a class="pts-vp-en" id="bd.2.28"></a> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np3:20.19"
msgid "aṭṭhārase uppanne …"
msgstr "eighteen days after …"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np3:20.20"
msgid "ekūnavīse uppanne …"
msgstr "nineteen days after …"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np3:20.21"
msgid "vīse uppanne mūlacīvare paccāsācīvaraṃ uppajjati, dasāhā kāretabbaṃ."
msgstr "twenty days after he received the original robe-cloth, it must be made into a robe within ten days."

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np3:20.22"
msgid "Ekavīse uppanne mūlacīvare paccāsācīvaraṃ uppajjati, navāhā kāretabbaṃ."
msgstr "If he receives the expected robe-cloth twenty-one days after he received the original robe-cloth, it must be made into a robe within nine days."

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np3:20.23"
msgid "Dvāvīse uppanne … pe …"
msgstr "If he receives the expected robe-cloth twenty-two days after he received the original robe-cloth, it must be made into a robe within eight days. …"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np3:20.24"
msgid "tevīse uppanne …"
msgstr "twenty-three days after …"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np3:20.25"
msgid "catuvīse uppanne …"
msgstr "twenty-four days after …"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np3:20.26"
msgid "pañcavīse uppanne …"
msgstr "twenty-five days after …"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np3:20.27"
msgid "chabbīse uppanne …"
msgstr "twenty-six days after …"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np3:20.28"
msgid "sattavīse uppanne …"
msgstr "twenty-seven days after …"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np3:20.29"
msgid "aṭṭhavīse uppanne …"
msgstr "twenty-eight days after …"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np3:20.30"
msgid "ekūnatiṃse uppanne mūlacīvare paccāsācīvaraṃ uppajjati, ekāhaṃ kāretabbaṃ …"
msgstr "If he receives the expected robe-cloth twenty-nine days after he received the original robe-cloth, it must be made into a robe within one day."

#. <span class="note" hidden>Again, according to the commentarial way of counting this refers to the twenty-ninth dawn after the original cloth was received. See the previous note.</span> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np3:20.31"
msgid "tiṃse uppanne mūlacīvare paccāsācīvaraṃ uppajjati, tadaheva adhiṭṭhātabbaṃ vikappetabbaṃ vissajjetabbaṃ."
msgstr "If he receives the expected robe-cloth thirty days after he received the original robe-cloth, it must be determined, transferred, or given away on that very day."

#. <span class="note" hidden>That is, on the thirtieth dawn after he received the original robe-cloth.</span> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np3:20.32"
msgid "No ce adhiṭṭheyya vā vikappeyya vā vissajjeyya vā, ekatiṃse aruṇuggamane nissaggiyaṃ hoti."
msgstr "If he does not determine it, transfer it, or give it away, it becomes subject to relinquishment at dawn on the thirty-first day."

#. </span></p><hr><p>
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np3:20.33"
msgid "Nissajjitabbaṃ saṃghassa vā gaṇassa vā puggalassa vā."
msgstr "The robe-cloth should be relinquished to the Order, a group, or an individual."

#. <span class="kamma"> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np3:20.34"
msgid "Evañca pana, bhikkhave, nissajjitabbaṃ …"
msgstr "“And, monks, it should be relinquished in this way. …"

#. <span class="add"> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np3:20.35"
msgid "pe …"
msgstr "To be expanded as in <a href=\"/en/pi-tv-bu-vb-np1/23-29\">Relinquishment 1, paragraphs 13–17</a>, with appropriate substitutions. …"

#. </span> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np3:20.36"
msgid "idaṃ me, bhante, akālacīvaraṃ māsātikkantaṃ nissaggiyaṃ,"
msgstr "‘Venerables, this out-of-season robe-cloth which I have kept for more than a month is to be relinquished."

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np3:20.37"
msgid "imāhaṃ saṃghassa nissajjāmīti … pe …"
msgstr "I relinquish it to the Order.’ …"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np3:20.38"
msgid "dadeyyāti … pe …"
msgstr "the Order should give …"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np3:20.39"
msgid "dadeyyunti … pe …"
msgstr "you should give …"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np3:20.40"
msgid "āyasmato dammīti."
msgstr "‘I give this robe-cloth back to you.’”"

#. </span></p><hr><p><a class="sc" id="16"></a><a class="pts-cs" id="bu-np.3.2.3"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="1936"></a> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np3:21.1"
msgid "Visabhāge uppanne mūlacīvare paccāsācīvaraṃ uppajjati, rattiyo ca sesā honti, na akāmā kāretabbaṃ."
msgstr "If he obtains the expected robe-cloth, but it is different from the robe-cloth originally obtained, and there are days remaining, he does not have to make a robe if he does not want to."

#. </p><h2>
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np3:22.1"
msgid ""
msgstr "Permutations"

#. </h2><p><a class="sc" id="17"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="1937"></a> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np3:22.2"
msgid "Māsātikkante atikkantasaññī, nissaggiyaṃ pācittiyaṃ."
msgstr "If it is more than a month and he perceives it as more than a month, he commits an offense entailing relinquishment and confession."

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np3:22.3"
msgid "Māsātikkante vematiko nissaggiyaṃ pācittiyaṃ."
msgstr "If it is more than a month, but he is unsure if it is, he commits an offense entailing relinquishment and confession."

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np3:22.4"
msgid "Māsātikkante anatikkantasaññī nissaggiyaṃ pācittiyaṃ."
msgstr "If it is more than a month, but he perceives it as less than a month, he commits an offense entailing relinquishment and confession."

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np3:22.5"
msgid "Anadhiṭṭhite adhiṭṭhitasaññī … pe …"
msgstr "If it is undetermined, but he perceives it as determined, he commits an offense entailing relinquishment and confession."

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np3:22.6"
msgid "avikappite vikappitasaññī …"
msgstr "If it is not transferred, but he perceives it as transferred, he commits an offense entailing relinquishment and confession."

#. <a class="pts-vp-en" id="bd.2.29"></a> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np3:22.7"
msgid "avissajjite vissajjitasaññī …"
msgstr "If it is not given away, but he perceives it as given away, he commits an offense entailing relinquishment and confession."

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np3:22.8"
msgid "anaṭṭhe naṭṭhasaññī …"
msgstr "If it is not lost, but he perceives it as lost, he commits an offense entailing relinquishment and confession."

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np3:22.9"
msgid "avinaṭṭhe vinaṭṭhasaññī …"
msgstr "If it is not destroyed, but he perceives it as destroyed, he commits an offense entailing relinquishment and confession."

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np3:22.10"
msgid "adaḍḍhe daḍḍhasaññī …"
msgstr "If it is not burnt, but he perceives it as burnt, he commits an offense entailing relinquishment and confession."

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np3:22.11"
msgid "avilutte viluttasaññī, nissaggiyaṃ pācittiyaṃ."
msgstr "If it is not stolen, but he perceives it as stolen, he commits an offense entailing relinquishment and confession."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="18"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="1938"></a><strong class="rule"> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np3:23.1"
msgid "Nissaggiyaṃ cīvaraṃ anissajjitvā paribhuñjati, āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr "If he uses robe-cloth which should be relinquished without first relinquishing it, he commits an offense of wrong conduct."

#. </strong> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np3:23.2"
msgid "Māsānatikkante atikkantasaññī, āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr "If it is less than a month, but he perceives it as more than a month, he commits an offense of wrong conduct."

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np3:23.3"
msgid "Māsānatikkante vematiko, āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr "If it is less than a month, but he is unsure if it is, he commits an offense of wrong conduct."

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np3:23.4"
msgid "Māsānatikkante anatikkantasaññī, anāpatti."
msgstr "If it is less than a month and he perceives it as less than a month, there is no offense."

#. </p><h2>
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np3:24.1"
msgid ""
msgstr "Non-offenses"

#. </h2><p><a class="sc" id="19"></a><a class="pts-cs" id="bu-np.3.2.4"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="1939"></a> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np3:24.2"
msgid "Anāpatti—"
msgstr "There is no offense:"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np3:24.3"
msgid "antomāse adhiṭṭheti, vikappeti, vissajjeti, nassati, vinassati, ḍayhati, acchinditvā gaṇhanti, vissāsaṃ gaṇhanti,"
msgstr "if within a month it has been determined, transferred, given away, lost, destroyed, burnt, stolen, or taken on trust;"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np3:24.4"
msgid "ummattakassa,"
msgstr "if he is insane;"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np3:24.5"
msgid "ādikammikassāti."
msgstr "if he is the first offender."

#. </p><hr><p class="endsutta"><a class="sc" id="20"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="1940"></a> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np3:25.1"
msgid "Tatiyakathinasikkhāpadaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ tatiyaṃ."
msgstr "The third rule, the third training rule on the robe-making season, is finished."

